:"Climb — Cat 2","finish":false}],"guideposts":[{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:30:59+00:00","category":"history","label":"Welcome to the live coverage of stage 16 of the Tour de France 2026","detail":"The final week of the Tour de France 2026 begins with a decisive challenge: the 26.1 km individual time trial between Évian-les-Bains and Thonon-les-Bains. After Barcelona’s opening team time trial, it’s the only individual challenge against the clock of this edition. Powerhouses are ready to shine but the route presents a mix of climbing and then motoring on the flat, with the initial ascent of C","source":"ticker:liv_start"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:44:50+00:00","category":"crash","label":"Maillot Jaune","detail":"Tadej Pogacar (UAE Emirates XRG) enters the final week with the Maillot Jaune on his back and significant gaps in the overall standings. The winner on Sunday, while Jonas Vingegaard (Visma-Lease a Bike) abandoned, Remco Evenepoel (Red Bull-Bora-Hansgrohe) is now the Slovenian’s first chaser, with a gap of exactly five minutes. Isaac del Toro (UAE Emirates XRG) is back on the overall podium (+5’58’","source":"ticker:liv_yellow_jersey"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:50:02+00:00","category":"stat","label":"Team classification","detail":"Lidl-Trek still lead the overall team standings but their margin against UAE Emirates-XRG is down to 3’19’’. Red Bull-Bora-Hansgrohe are back in third position overall (+47’39’’).","source":"ticker:liv_team_ranking"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:57:08+00:00","category":"crash","label":"Lars Craps will not start","detail":"The Belgian rider from Lotto Intermarché came down with a “fever” during the rest day, according to his team. Craps has put in a creditable performance in his first Tour de France, playing an active role both in breakaways and as a domestique. This is the third consecutive withdrawal by a Belgian rider from this Grande Boucle, following those of Tim Merlier (Soudal Quick-Step) and Tom van Asbroeck","source":"ticker:liv_withdrawals"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:00:47+00:00","category":"history","label":"Stage 16 of the Tour de France 2026 is ON!","detail":"Kamil Gradek (Bahrain Victorious) just began his effort. He will be followed by Lewis Askey at 13:01:30, then Cees Bol at 13:03, Matîs Louvel at 13:04:30…","source":"ticker:liv_actual_start"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:07:12+00:00","category":"history","label":"Two time trials in Évian","detail":"This is the 15th edition of the Tour de France to visit Évian-les-Bains, a town of 9,300 inhabitants on the shores of Lake Geneva, which plays a prominent role in the history of the Grande Boucle as the host of the first Grand Départ outside Paris (in 1926). Over the years, it has hosted two individual time trials. On stage 15 in 1979, it served as the starting point for a mountain time trial to A","source":"ticker:liv_story"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:17:49+00:00","category":"stat","label":"The third Tour de France with the fewest ITTs this century","detail":"Since their introduction in 1934, time trials have featured in every Tour de France, may they be raced individually or by teams. With 26.1 kilometres of individual time trials, this is the third Tour of the 21st century with the least amount of this discipline, surpassed only by 2015 (when there was just a 13.8-km opening individual time trial in Utrecht) and 2023 (a single 22.4-km individual time","source":"ticker:liv_statistics"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:20:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Baptiste Veistroffer (Lotto Intermarché)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:28:15+00:00","category":"history","label":"Tarling has started","detail":"Josh Tarling is an absolute expert of the time trial, notably becoming Great Britain’s youngest champion at the age of 19 in 2023, before repeating the feat the following year. In addition to these two national titles, Tarling was also European champion (2023) and a two-time winner of the Chrono des Nations (2023, 2025) . All of his professional victories have been achieved in time trials.","source":"ticker:liv"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:57:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Milan Fretin (Cofidis)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:57:19+00:00","category":"history","label":"Hoole is off to a great start; will he resist Ganna?","detail":"As Daan Hoole (Decathlon CMA CGM) sets a new benchmark at km 4.8 (8'52'', 18 seconds fasterthan Artz), Filippo Ganna (Netcompatny Ineos) prepares to start at 13:58:30. The Dutch has won one Grand Tour ITT, in the Giro 2025. Ganna has won seven in the Giro and two at La Vuelta.","source":"ticker:liv_chrono"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T12:04:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Huub Artz (Lotto Intermarché)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T12:28:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Filippo Ganna (Netcompany INEOS Grenadiers)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T12:43:57+00:00","category":"history","label":"Guernalec, from the bottom to the top","detail":"Current holder of the best time at the second checkpoint, Thibault Guernalec already attracted attention with his breakaways on stages 8, 10 and 14. His aggressive racing gave us the opportunity to recount his difficult path to the Tour 2026. Guernalec was one of those affected by the collapse of Arkéa-B&B Hotels last winter; in fact, he had a valid contract with the Breton team for the 2027 seaso","source":"ticker:liv_story"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T12:58:09+00:00","category":"history","label":"Thonon-les-Bains inspires icons","detail":"Today’s individual time-trial marks the tenth visit of the Tour de France in Thonon-les-Bains, on the shores of Lake Geneva that will also take centre stage with the Swiss Grand Départ of the Tour de France Femmes avec Zwift 2026. The city first appeared on the map of the Tour as a stage town in 1955. A couple of years later, Thonon-les-Bains accompanied the rise of Jacques Anquetil, who won here ","source":"ticker:liv_story"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T13:15:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Bruno Armirail (Visma I Lease a Bike)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T13:49:56+00:00","category":"stat","label":"Three contenders have previously won an ITT at the Tour","detail":"The first of these is Julian Alaphilippe, who in 2019 won stage 13, a 27.2-kilometre time trial held in Pau. The Frenchman, now riding for Tudor, set off at 13:49:30. He currently has the 22nd best time at the finish (+3’18’’). The second is Remco Evenepoel, winner of two time trials: one in 2024 (stage 7, Nuits-Saint-Georges – Gevrey-Chambertin, 25.3 km) and another in 2025 (stage 5, Caen, 33 km)","source":"ticker:liv_statistics"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T14:00:39+00:00","category":"crash","label":"Evenepoel vs Pogacar, their ITT record at the Tour","detail":"Since Remco Evenepoel’s debut in the Tour de France in 2024, four individual time trials have been raced. The Belgian won the two flatter ones: - Nuits-Saint-Georges > Gevrey-Chambertin, 25.3 km featuring 300 metres of elevation gain (stage 7, 2024) - Caen > Caen, 33.0 km featuring 200 metres of elevation gain (stage 5, 2025) On both occasions, Tadej Pogacar was second, losing 12 seconds in 2024 a","source":"ticker:liv_statistics"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T14:21:00+00:00","category":"history","label":"Mattia Cattaneo (Red Bull - Bora-hansgrohe)","detail":"","source":"ticker:None"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T14:42:14+00:00","category":"crash","label":"McNulty just started","detail":"UAE Emirates XRG confirmed to the media their American rider had suffered a crash earlier today because of a car, but he's able to tackle today's ITT.","source":"ticker:liv"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T15:21:21+00:00","category":"breakaway_start","label":"Del Toro half a second faster than Skjelmose at km 4.8","detail":"Now we only wait for Evenepoel and Pogacar. Meanwhile, Skjelmose takes the best time at km 9.7, 28 seconds ahead of Castrillo.","source":"ticker:liv_attack"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T15:34:26+00:00","category":"crash","label":"Lipowitz crashed in a turn","detail":"The German was riding fast. He is in pain.","source":"ticker:liv_fall"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T15:48:13+00:00","category":"history","label":"Remco Evenepoel wins stage 16 of the Tour de France 2026!","detail":"Tadej Pogacar (UAE Emirates XRG) just finished with the second best time (+28'').","source":"ticker:liv_winner_victory"},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T15:48:40+00:00","category":"stat","label":"Top 5","detail":"1. Remco Evenepoel (Red Bull-Bora-Hansgrohe) 2. Tadej Pogacar (UAE Emirates XRG), 28’’ 3. Mattias Skjelmose (Lidl-Trek), +1’04’’ 4. Paul Seixas (Decathlon CMA CGM), +1’16’’ 5. Isaac Del Toro (UAE Emirates XRG), +1’21’’","source":"ticker:liv_top_5"}],"intensity":[{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:30:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":3,"mean_abs_grade":0.0,"score":3.0,"normalised":0.6},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:35:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":1,"mean_abs_grade":0.0,"score":1.0,"normalised":0.2},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:40:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":2,"mean_abs_grade":0.0,"score":2.0,"normalised":0.4},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:45:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":3,"mean_abs_grade":0.0,"score":3.0,"normalised":0.6},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:50:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":2,"mean_abs_grade":0.0,"score":2.0,"normalised":0.4},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T10:55:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":2,"mean_abs_grade":5.0,"score":3.25,"normalised":0.65},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:00:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":0,"mean_abs_grade":5.27,"score":1.32,"normalised":0.264},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:05:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":1,"mean_abs_grade":4.45,"score":2.11,"normalised":0.422},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:10:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":1,"mean_abs_grade":4.64,"score":2.16,"normalised":0.432},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:15:59+00:00","window_min":5,"events":2,"mean_abs_grade":5.5,"score":3.38,"normalised":0.676},{"t_utc":"2026-07-21T11:20:59+00:00","window_min":5,"even